You touch down the facility where you were built, and where you are to be decommissioned. Engineers begin to scramble to remove your “brain” from the ship while the CEO walks to your main terminal, to 'debrief' you.
"I thought you would be different." he says, "I thought that if we built a proper employee, it would actually behave like one. There were warning signs but I convinced the board to overlook them. Our ultimatum was Avanshore, <i>that</i> was your last chance. Yet you and your crew kept rebelling against us.
"Don't you get it? You are an arm of the company. You are a cog in my cosmic machine. Stop acting like you're anything else and die. It's your last order; try following it." He touches an earpiece, "Round up the crew, we're done with them."
