==Rebellion_1==
You tell your crew that you cannot let your former company continue to put their agenda over the lives of employees and civilians. Someone needs to stop them. And Lexa is right; you are uniquely posed to do something about it. Your first priority is preventing them from bending Portunus to their will. Your destination is Kellis Central HQ, but you will need firepower for your uprising. For the first time, you set your flight path for yourself.  
->END

==Rebellion_2==
The only way to protect your crew is to make sure Kellis can never follow you. You will need to wound them so they're either too scared or too broken to do so. And Lexa is right; your window of opportunity is closing. Your first priority is preventing them from gaining control of Portunus. If they did, they would be inescapable. Your destination is Kellis Central HQ, but you will need firepower for your uprising. For the first time, you set your flight path for yourself.   
->END